        <IsA>app:gui</IsA>
        <Summary>A VirtualBox installation tool for Pardus GNU/Linux</Summary>
        <Description>pavi is a graphical script, which installs Sun xVM VirtualBox on Pardus GNU/Linux automaticly. You can choose between setup modes like install VirtualBox from an existing file (VirtualBox universal "All distributions i386" RUN-file), or removing and upgrading VirtualBox PAVI can of course download and install it automaticly form the internet and install it. During the boot PAVI checks like a DKMS, if VirtulaBox Linux kernel modules are existing. If not, than it will build them. This feature is usefull, if user has updated the Linux kernel.</Description>
        <Archive type="tarbz2" sha1sum="1f0195e869703d061ca3a237da44d690822ac2a7">http://pakete.pardususer.de/quellarchive/pavi-2.4.tar.bz2</Archive>
    </Source>

    <Package>
        <Name>pavi</Name>
        <RuntimeDependencies>
            <Dependency>bash</Dependency>
            <Dependency>coreutils</Dependency>
            <Dependency>dialog</Dependency>
            <Dependency>grep</Dependency>
            <Dependency>sed</Dependency>
            <Dependency>wget</Dependency>
        </RuntimeDependencies>
        <Files>
			<Path fileType="data">/etc/init.d/</Path>
            <Path fileType="data">/usr/share/applications/</Path>
            <Path fileType="data">/usr/share/pixmaps/</Path>
            <Path fileType="doc">/usr/share/doc/</Path>
            <Path fileType="executable">/usr/bin/</Path>
        </Files>
        <AdditionalFiles>
            <AdditionalFile owner="root" permission="0644" target="/usr/share/applications/pavi.desktop">pavi.desktop</AdditionalFile>
        </AdditionalFiles>
    </Package>

